    <activity>
        <task workspace="0.25in">
            <statement>
                <p>
                    The <term>vertical intercept</term> of a mathematical model is the value where the graph crosses the vertical axis. It is also called the <term>initial value</term> because it is the output when the input is 0. What is the vertical intercept of your graph in <xref ref="xcel-summer-electricity"/> part (e)?
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
        <task workspace="0.5in">
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Suppose that Theo used <m>k</m> kWh of energy in a summer month. Find a formula for <m>B</m>, Theo's bill.
